Arts Fulshear is... Remember that imaginary friend you had when you were little, or the plays you put on in the backyard? Remember the worlds you created with just a crayon and a piece of paper?
At Arts Fulshear we're passionate about encouraging creativity and creative play for all children. Our classes allow children from Kindergarten on to learn to express themselves creatively, letting imaginations run wild!
A group of educators and artists with a passion for the visual and performing arts started Arts Fulshear in 2011, and we've been growing since, providing classes for young and old. 
We need space for theater classes and productions and for art classes. We've been begging and borrowing, and we're ready for a real space! With your help, we can acquire temporary space and then build a visual and performing arts center that serves children from all over South Texas.   Arts Fulshear needs...We need $7,000 a month for theater and classroom space to adequately serve our community.You'll get... 
$1,000 or more--An art print by one of our adult artists and all the perks below; 
$500 or more--All the perks below;
$100 or more--Two coffee mugs with Fulshear Heart logo or "The Sweet Life";
$50 or more--An Arts Fulshear t-shirt;
$25 or more--Five greeing cards with prints of children's art, and
$10 or more--Our undying gratitude and the knowledge that you helped bring art to a child!
 If we don't reach our goal of raising enough money for space, all money raised will fund our programs for children, so more deserving children will receive art and theater lessons.    Your impact... 
$100--supplies for a six-week art class for twenty children, or tuition for one child.
$500 will fund one "Meet the Masters" unit for an entire elementary school!
$1,000 --will fund an outdoor sculpture or a mural!
$7,000--rent on four classrooms, an office and a theater space for one year, helping us keep our tuition affordable and allowing us to offer more scholarships.    We're challenged by...  Finding good people is always a challenge. Our focus over the past month has been to recruit talented and qualified teachers. We're fortunate to have found teachers who love to work with young children, and have the background to know how.    You can help by... Just because you can't contribute doesn't mean you can't help:  Ask folks to get the word out and make some noise about Arts Fulshear and our campaign;
Volunteer if you're in the area; and  Use the Indiegogo share tools!
